<<<<<<<<<<=====PROBLEM STATEMENT=====>>>>>>>>>>
Assume that there is a button named testButton on an HTML page.
There is no event associated with clicking this button on the HTML page.
I want to add a custom event named testEvent to that page only through GTM, without making any changes to the HTML page's code.
When the button is clicked, the custom event testEvent should fire.
After that, I want to track the testEvent custom event using GTM.
Describe step by step in English what needs to be done to achieve this.
============================================
Sure! Below is a step-by-step guide in English to fire a custom event named `testEvent` using Google Tag Manager (GTM) when a button with the ID `testButton` is clicked ‚Äî without modifying the HTML page itself.

‚úÖ Objective:
- Button ID: `testButton`
- No existing click handler in HTML
- Goal: Fire a GTM custom event `testEvent` on click, using only GTM

üîß Steps in Google Tag Manager

1. Create a Trigger for Button Click

1. Go to your GTM container.
2. Navigate to Triggers > Click on ‚ÄúNew‚Äù.
3. Name it: `Click - testButton`
4. Choose Trigger Type: `Click ‚Äì All Elements`
5. Configure Trigger:
   - Select: `Some Clicks`
   - Condition: `Click ID` ‚Üí `equals` ‚Üí `testButton`
6. Save the trigger.

2. Enable Built-In Variables

Make sure the following built-in variables are enabled:
- `Click ID`
- `Click Classes`
- `Click Text`

To check:
- Go to Variables
- Click Configure (top-right)
- Tick the checkboxes for all Click-related variables.

3. Create a Tag to Push `testEvent` to Data Layer

1. Go to Tags > Click ‚ÄúNew‚Äù
2. Name it: `Push testEvent to DataLayer`
3. Choose Tag Type: `Custom HTML`
4. Paste the following code:
   ```html
   <script>
     window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
     window.dataLayer.push({
       event: 'testEvent'
     });
   </script>
   ```
5. Trigger: Choose the previously created trigger `Click - testButton`
6. Save the tag.

4. Create a Tag to Track `testEvent`

Now that the event `testEvent` will be pushed to the data layer, create a listener tag:

1. Go to Triggers > Click ‚ÄúNew‚Äù
2. Name it: `Custom Event - testEvent`
3. Trigger Type: `Custom Event`
4. Event Name: `testEvent` (case-sensitive)
5. Save the trigger

5. Create a Final Tracking Tag

Use this trigger to fire your tracking pixel, GA4 event, or test tag.

1. Go to Tags > Click New
2. Name: `GA4 - Event - testEvent` (or anything meaningful)
3. Tag Type: e.g., GA4 Event Tag
4. Configure:
   - Measurement ID: Your GA4 Measurement ID
   - Event Name: `testEvent`
5. Trigger: `Custom Event - testEvent`
6. Save

6. Test in Preview Mode

1. Click Preview in GTM.
2. Enter the URL of the page containing the `testButton`.
3. Click the `testButton`.
4. In the Tag Assistant preview pane:
   - Confirm the `Push testEvent to DataLayer` tag fired
   - Confirm the GA4 `testEvent` tag fired

